{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"Do you know"},{"time":4000,"text":"how many species of flowering plants there are?"},{"time":7000,"text":"There are a quarter of a million -- at least those are the ones we know about --"},{"time":10000,"text":"a quarter of a million species of flowering plants."},{"time":13000,"text":"And flowers are a real bugger."},{"time":15000,"text":"They're really difficult for plants to produce."},{"time":17000,"text":"They take an enormous amount of energy and a lot of resources."},{"time":20000,"text":"Why would they go to that bother?"},{"time":22000,"text":"And the answer of course, like so many things in the world,"},{"time":24000,"text":"is sex."},{"time":26000,"text":"I know what's on your mind when you're looking at these pictures."},{"time":30000,"text":"And the reason that sexual reproduction is so important --"},{"time":33000,"text":"there are lots of other things that plants can do to reproduce."},{"time":36000,"text":"You can take cuttings;"},{"time":38000,"text":"they can sort of have sex with themselves;"},{"time":40000,"text":"they can pollinate themselves."},{"time":42000,"text":"But they really need to spread their genes"},{"time":44000,"text":"to mix with other genes"},{"time":46000,"text":"so that they can adapt to environmental niches."},{"time":48000,"text":"Evolution works that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"Now the way that plants transmit that information"},{"time":52000,"text":"is through pollen."},{"time":54000,"text":"Some of you may have seen some of these pictures before."},{"time":56000,"text":"As I say, every home should have a scanning electron microscope"},{"time":58000,"text":"to be able to see these."},{"time":60000,"text":"And there is as many different kinds of pollen"},{"time":62000,"text":"as there are flowering plants."},{"time":64000,"text":"And that's actually rather useful for forensics and so on."},{"time":67000,"text":"Most pollen that causes hay fever for us"},{"time":70000,"text":"is from plants that use the wind"},{"time":72000,"text":"to disseminate the pollen,"},{"time":74000,"text":"and that's a very inefficient process,"},{"time":77000,"text":"which is why it gets up our noses so much."},{"time":79000,"text":"Because you have to chuck out masses and masses of it,"},{"time":81000,"text":"hoping that your sex cells, your male sex cells,"},{"time":84000,"text":"which are held within the pollen,"},{"time":86000,"text":"will somehow reach another flower just by chance."},{"time":88000,"text":"So all the grasses, which means all of the cereal crops,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and most of the trees"},{"time":93000,"text":"have wind-borne pollen."},{"time":95000,"text":"But most species"},{"time":97000,"text":"actually use insects to do their bidding,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and that's more intelligent in a way,"},{"time":102000,"text":"because the pollen, they don't need so much of it."},{"time":105000,"text":"The insects"},{"time":107000,"text":"and other species"},{"time":110000,"text":"can take the pollen,"},{"time":112000,"text":"transfer it directly to where it's required."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"So we're aware, obviously, of the relationship"},{"time":117000,"text":"between insects and plants."},{"time":119000,"text":"There's a symbiotic relationship there,"},{"time":121000,"text":"whether it's flies or birds or bees,"},{"time":124000,"text":"they're getting something in return,"},{"time":126000,"text":"and that something in return is generally nectar."},{"time":129000,"text":"Sometimes that symbiosis"},{"time":131000,"text":"has led to wonderful adaptations --"},{"time":133000,"text":"the hummingbird hawk-moth"},{"time":135000,"text":"is beautiful in its adaptation."},{"time":137000,"text":"The plant gets something,"},{"time":139000,"text":"and the hawk-moth spreads the pollen somewhere else."},{"time":143000,"text":"Plants have evolved"},{"time":145000,"text":"to create little landing strips here and there"},{"time":147000,"text":"for bees that might have lost their way."},{"time":149000,"text":"There are markings on many plants"},{"time":151000,"text":"that look like other insects."},{"time":154000,"text":"These are the anthers of a lily,"},{"time":156000,"text":"cleverly done"},{"time":158000,"text":"so that when the unsuspecting insect"},{"time":160000,"text":"lands on it,"},{"time":162000,"text":"the anther flips up and whops it on the back"},{"time":164000,"text":"with a great load of pollen that it then goes to another plant with."},{"time":167000,"text":"And there's an orchid"},{"time":170000,"text":"that might look to you as if it's got jaws,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and in a way, it has; it forces the insect to crawl out,"},{"time":175000,"text":"getting covered in pollen that it takes somewhere else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Orchids: there are 20,000, at least,"},{"time":181000,"text":"species of orchids --"},{"time":183000,"text":"amazingly, amazingly diverse."},{"time":185000,"text":"And they get up to all sorts of tricks."},{"time":187000,"text":"They have to try and attract pollinators"},{"time":190000,"text":"to do their bidding."},{"time":192000,"text":"This orchid, known as Darwin's orchid,"},{"time":195000,"text":"because it's one that he studied"},{"time":197000,"text":"and made a wonderful prediction when he saw it --"},{"time":199000,"text":"you can see that there's a very long nectar tube"},{"time":202000,"text":"that descends down"},{"time":204000,"text":"from the orchid."},{"time":206000,"text":"And basically what the insect has to do --"},{"time":208000,"text":"we're in the middle of the flower --"},{"time":210000,"text":"it has to stick its little proboscis"},{"time":212000,"text":"right into the middle of that"},{"time":214000,"text":"and all the way down that nectar tube"},{"time":216000,"text":"to get to the nectar."},{"time":218000,"text":"And Darwin said, looking at this flower,"},{"time":221000,"text":"\"I guess something has coevolved with this.\""},{"time":223000,"text":"And sure enough,"},{"time":225000,"text":"there's the insect."},{"time":227000,"text":"And I mean, normally it kind of rolls it away,"},{"time":229000,"text":"but in its erect form,"},{"time":231000,"text":"that's what it looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"Now you can imagine"},{"time":236000,"text":"that if nectar"},{"time":238000,"text":"is such a valuable thing"},{"time":241000,"text":"and expensive for the plant to produce"},{"time":243000,"text":"and it attracts lots of pollinators,"},{"time":246000,"text":"then, just as in human sex,"},{"time":248000,"text":"people might start to deceive."},{"time":250000,"text":"They might say, \"I've got a bit of nectar. Do you want to come and get it?\""},{"time":253000,"text":"Now this is a plant."},{"time":256000,"text":"This is a plant here"},{"time":258000,"text":"that insects in South Africa just love,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and they've evolved with a long proboscis"},{"time":265000,"text":"to get the nectar at the bottom."},{"time":267000,"text":"And this is the mimic."},{"time":269000,"text":"So this is a plant that is mimicking the first plant."},{"time":272000,"text":"And here is the long-probosced fly"},{"time":275000,"text":"that has not gotten any nectar from the mimic,"},{"time":278000,"text":"because the mimic doesn't give it any nectar. It thought it would get some."},{"time":281000,"text":"So not only has the fly"},{"time":283000,"text":"not got the nectar from the mimic plant,"},{"time":285000,"text":"it's also -- if you look very closely"},{"time":287000,"text":"just at the head end, you can see that it's got a bit of pollen"},{"time":290000,"text":"that it would be transmitting to another plant,"},{"time":292000,"text":"if only some botanist hadn't come along"},{"time":294000,"text":"and stuck it to a blue piece of card."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"Now deceit carries on through the plant kingdom."},{"time":304000,"text":"This flower with its black dots:"},{"time":306000,"text":"they might look like black dots to us,"},{"time":308000,"text":"but if I tell you, to a male insect of the right species,"},{"time":311000,"text":"that looks like two females"},{"time":313000,"text":"who are really, really hot to trot."},{"time":315000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":317000,"text":"And when the insect gets there and lands on it,"},{"time":320000,"text":"dousing itself in pollen, of course, that it's going to take to another plant,"},{"time":323000,"text":"if you look at the every-home-should-have-one scanning electron microscope picture,"},{"time":327000,"text":"you can see that there are actually some patterning there,"},{"time":329000,"text":"which is three-dimensional."},{"time":331000,"text":"So it probably even feels good for the insect,"},{"time":334000,"text":"as well as looking good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"And these electron microscope pictures --"},{"time":339000,"text":"here's one of an orchid mimicking an insect --"},{"time":342000,"text":"you can see that different parts of the structure"},{"time":345000,"text":"have different colors and different textures to our eye,"},{"time":348000,"text":"have very, very different textures"},{"time":350000,"text":"to what an insect might perceive."},{"time":353000,"text":"And this one is evolved to mimic"},{"time":355000,"text":"a glossy metallic surface"},{"time":358000,"text":"you see on some beetles."},{"time":360000,"text":"And under the scanning electron microscope,"},{"time":363000,"text":"you can see the surface there --"},{"time":366000,"text":"really quite different from the other surfaces we looked at."},{"time":370000,"text":"Sometimes the whole plant"},{"time":372000,"text":"mimics an insect, even to us."},{"time":375000,"text":"I mean, I think that looks like some sort of flying animal or beast."},{"time":378000,"text":"It's a wonderful, amazing thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"This one's clever. It's called obsidian."},{"time":384000,"text":"I think of it as insidium sometimes."},{"time":386000,"text":"To the right species of bee,"},{"time":389000,"text":"this looks like another very aggressive bee,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and it goes and bonks it on the head lots and lots of times to try and drive it away,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and, of course, covers itself with pollen."},{"time":396000,"text":"The other thing it does"},{"time":398000,"text":"is that this plant mimics another orchid"},{"time":401000,"text":"that has a wonderful store"},{"time":404000,"text":"of food for insects."},{"time":406000,"text":"And this one doesn't have anything for them."},{"time":408000,"text":"So it's deceiving on two levels --"},{"time":410000,"text":"fabulous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"Here we see ylang ylang,"},{"time":416000,"text":"the component of many perfumes."},{"time":418000,"text":"I actually smelt someone with some on earlier."},{"time":421000,"text":"And the flowers don't really have to be that gaudy."},{"time":423000,"text":"They're sending out a fantastic array of scent"},{"time":426000,"text":"to any insect that'll have it."},{"time":429000,"text":"This one doesn't smell so good."},{"time":431000,"text":"This is a flower"},{"time":433000,"text":"that really, really smells pretty nasty"},{"time":436000,"text":"and is designed, again, evolved,"},{"time":439000,"text":"to look like carrion."},{"time":442000,"text":"So flies love this."},{"time":444000,"text":"They fly in and they pollinate."},{"time":447000,"text":"This, which is helicodiceros,"},{"time":451000,"text":"is also known as dead horse arum."},{"time":454000,"text":"I don't know what a dead horse actually smells like,"},{"time":456000,"text":"but this one probably smells pretty much like it."},{"time":458000,"text":"It's really horrible."},{"time":460000,"text":"And blowflies just can't help themselves."},{"time":462000,"text":"They fly into this thing,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and they fly all the way down it."},{"time":466000,"text":"They lay their eggs in it,"},{"time":468000,"text":"thinking it's a nice bit of carrion,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and not realizing that there's no food for the eggs, that the eggs are going to die,"},{"time":473000,"text":"but the plant, meanwhile, has benefited,"},{"time":476000,"text":"because the bristles release"},{"time":478000,"text":"and the flies disappear"},{"time":480000,"text":"to pollinate the next flower -- fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483000,"text":"Here's arum, arum maculatum,"},{"time":485000,"text":"\"lords and ladies,\" or \"cuckoo-pint\" in this country."},{"time":488000,"text":"I photographed this thing last week in Dorset."},{"time":490000,"text":"This thing heats up"},{"time":492000,"text":"by about 15 degrees above ambient temperature --"},{"time":494000,"text":"amazing."},{"time":496000,"text":"And if you look down into it,"},{"time":498000,"text":"there's this sort of dam past the spadix,"},{"time":501000,"text":"flies get attracted by the heat --"},{"time":503000,"text":"which is boiling off volatile chemicals, little midges --"},{"time":505000,"text":"and they get trapped underneath in this container."},{"time":508000,"text":"They drink this fabulous nectar"},{"time":511000,"text":"and then they're all a bit sticky."},{"time":513000,"text":"At night they get covered in pollen,"},{"time":516000,"text":"which showers down over them,"},{"time":518000,"text":"and then the bristles that we saw above,"},{"time":520000,"text":"they sort of wilt and allow all these midges out, covered in pollen --"},{"time":523000,"text":"fabulous thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"Now if you think that's fabulous, this is one of my great favorites."},{"time":528000,"text":"This is the philodendron selloum."},{"time":531000,"text":"For anyone here from Brazil, you'll know about this plant."},{"time":534000,"text":"This is the most amazing thing."},{"time":536000,"text":"That sort of phallic bit there"},{"time":538000,"text":"is about a foot long."},{"time":540000,"text":"And it does something"},{"time":542000,"text":"that no other plant that I know of does,"},{"time":545000,"text":"and that is that when it flowers --"},{"time":547000,"text":"that's the spadix in the middle there --"},{"time":549000,"text":"for a period of about two days,"},{"time":552000,"text":"it metabolizes in a way"},{"time":554000,"text":"which is rather similar to mammals."},{"time":556000,"text":"So instead of having starch,"},{"time":558000,"text":"which is the food of plants,"},{"time":560000,"text":"it takes something rather similar to brown fat"},{"time":562000,"text":"and burns it at such a rate"},{"time":564000,"text":"that it's burning fat, metabolizing,"},{"time":567000,"text":"about the rate of a small cat."},{"time":570000,"text":"And that's twice the energy output, weight for weight,"},{"time":573000,"text":"than a hummingbird --"},{"time":575000,"text":"absolutely astonishing."},{"time":577000,"text":"This thing does something else which is unusual."},{"time":579000,"text":"Not only will it raise itself to 115 Fahrenheit,"},{"time":582000,"text":"43 or 44 degrees Centigrade, for two days,"},{"time":585000,"text":"but it keeps constant temperature."},{"time":588000,"text":"There's a thermoregulation mechanism in there"},{"time":590000,"text":"that keeps constant temperature."},{"time":592000,"text":"\"Now why does it do this,\" I hear you ask."},{"time":594000,"text":"Now wouldn't you know it,"},{"time":596000,"text":"there's some beetles that just love to make love at that temperature."},{"time":600000,"text":"And they get inside, and they get it all on."},{"time":603000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":605000,"text":"And the plant showers them with pollen,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and off they go and pollinate."},{"time":610000,"text":"And what a wonderful thing it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"Now most pollinators"},{"time":616000,"text":"that we think about are insects,"},{"time":618000,"text":"but actually in the tropics,"},{"time":620000,"text":"many birds and butterflies pollinate."},{"time":623000,"text":"And many of the tropical flowers are red,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and that's because butterflies and birds"},{"time":627000,"text":"see similarly to us, we think,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and can see the color red very well."},{"time":632000,"text":"But if you look at the spectrum,"},{"time":635000,"text":"birds and us, we see red, green and blue"},{"time":638000,"text":"and see that spectrum."},{"time":640000,"text":"Insects see green, blue and ultraviolet,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and they see various shades of ultraviolet."},{"time":644000,"text":"So there's something that goes on off the end there."},{"time":647000,"text":"\"And wouldn't it be great if we could somehow see what that is,\" I hear you ask."},{"time":650000,"text":"Well yes we can."},{"time":652000,"text":"So what is an insect seeing?"},{"time":655000,"text":"Last week I took these pictures of rock rose,"},{"time":657000,"text":"helianthemum, in Dorset."},{"time":659000,"text":"These are little yellow flowers like we all see,"},{"time":662000,"text":"little yellow flowers all over the place."},{"time":664000,"text":"And this is what it looks like with visible light."},{"time":667000,"text":"This is what it looks like if you take out the red."},{"time":670000,"text":"Most bees don't perceive red."},{"time":673000,"text":"And then I put some ultraviolet filters on my camera"},{"time":677000,"text":"and took a very, very long exposure"},{"time":680000,"text":"with the particular frequencies of ultraviolet light"},{"time":683000,"text":"and this is what I got."},{"time":685000,"text":"And that's a real fantastic bull's eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"Now we don't know"},{"time":690000,"text":"exactly what a bee sees,"},{"time":692000,"text":"any more than you know what I'm seeing"},{"time":694000,"text":"when I call this red."},{"time":697000,"text":"We can't know what's going on in -- let alone an insect's --"},{"time":700000,"text":"another human being's mind."},{"time":703000,"text":"But the contrast will look something like that,"},{"time":707000,"text":"so standing out a lot from the background."},{"time":709000,"text":"Here's another little flower --"},{"time":711000,"text":"different range of ultraviolet frequencies,"},{"time":714000,"text":"different filters"},{"time":716000,"text":"to match the pollinators."},{"time":718000,"text":"And that's the sort of thing that it would be seeing."},{"time":721000,"text":"Just in case you think"},{"time":723000,"text":"that all yellow flowers have this property --"},{"time":726000,"text":"no flower was damaged in the process of this shot;"},{"time":729000,"text":"it was just attached to the tripod,"},{"time":732000,"text":"not killed --"},{"time":734000,"text":"then under ultraviolet light,"},{"time":736000,"text":"look at that."},{"time":738000,"text":"And that could be the basis of a sunscreen"},{"time":740000,"text":"because sunscreens work by absorbing ultraviolet light."},{"time":742000,"text":"So maybe the chemical in that would be useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"Finally, there's one of evening primrose"},{"time":749000,"text":"that Bjorn Rorslett from Norway sent me --"},{"time":751000,"text":"fantastic hidden pattern."},{"time":753000,"text":"And I love the idea of something hidden."},{"time":755000,"text":"I think there's something poetic here,"},{"time":757000,"text":"that these pictures taken with ultraviolet filter,"},{"time":760000,"text":"the main use of that filter"},{"time":762000,"text":"is for astronomers to take pictures of Venus --"},{"time":765000,"text":"actually the clouds of Venus."},{"time":768000,"text":"That's the main use of that filter."},{"time":770000,"text":"Venus, of course, is the god of love and fertility,"},{"time":773000,"text":"which is the flower story."},{"time":775000,"text":"And just as flowers spend a lot of effort"},{"time":777000,"text":"trying to get pollinators to do their bidding,"},{"time":780000,"text":"they've also somehow managed to persuade us to plant great fields full of them"},{"time":783000,"text":"and give them to each other"},{"time":785000,"text":"at times of birth and death,"},{"time":789000,"text":"and particularly at marriage,"},{"time":791000,"text":"which, when you think of it,"},{"time":793000,"text":"is the moment that encapsulates"},{"time":795000,"text":"the transfer of genetic material"},{"time":798000,"text":"from one organism to another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}